  "description": "Two-oscillator source (source=4) with osc2Mix=0.65 and osc2Detune=0.22 — the two oscillators create beating interference patterns that the granulator then scatters. Grain size 180ms, density=12. posScatter=0.95 means grains are harvested from nearly random positions in the 4-second buffer. The beating frequency of the two detuned oscillators becomes temporally scattered — interference heard as spatial event rather than periodic rhythm. Sub filter at 2200Hz.",
  "tags": ["two-osc", "detuned", "scatter", "submerged", "beating", "interference", "spatial"],
  "macroLabels": ["SCATTER", "DRIFT", "COUPLING", "SPACE"],
